webLinks.linkText: Wollongong City Council - Music at the Drive-in
Hockey Dad - Alive at the Drive-In

properties.headline: Drive-in concerts - Friday 31 July to Sunday 2 August - BULLI Princes Highway at Grevillea Park Road
properties.otherAdvice:
Drive-in concerts will be held at Bulli Showgrounds on Friday, Saturday and Sunday with a capacity for 400 vehicles.

Friday and Saturday Hockey Dad Alive at the Drive-in ft The Pinheads from 6pm to 11pm approx on Friday and Saturday.

Sunday: Music at the Drive-in: Sons of the East drive-in concert at Bulli Showgrounds from 2pm to 5pm.

Motorists should allow extra travel time as traffic may be heavier than usual on the Princes Hwy approaching Grevillea Park Rd as attendees enter and exit Bulli Showgrounds.
properties.displayName: Drive-in concerts - Friday 31 July to Sunday 2 August

properties.headline: Super Rugby - Friday 24 July - MOORE PARK various roads incl Moore Park Rd, Anzac Pde, Lang Rd, Eastern Distributor approaching The SCG

arrangementAttachments.fileName: SCO_1080_MOORE PARK CENTRAL PEDESTRIAN BUS ACCESS MAP w strap_09JUL20_V013.pdf

properties.otherAdvice:
Super Rugby: Waratahs v Rebels at the SCG from 7:05pm until 8:35pm approx.

Traffic may be heavier than usual on Anzac Pde, Eastern Distributor, Moore Park Rd, Cleveland St and Lang Rd approaching Moore Park as fans travel to and from the game during Friday evening peak.

Driver Ave will also be partially closed before kick off and remain closed until crowds have cleared the precinct after full-time. 

Special event clearways will be in effect on various roads from 3pm until 11pm including sections of Moore Park Rd, Lang Rd, Albion St, Chalmers St, Fitzroy St, Flinders St and Foveaux St. 

Clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

arrangementElements.html:
Special event clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Parking Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed, call 132 701 to find its new location.

SURRY HILLS / MOORE PARK

FROM 6AM TO 11PM

  • Cleveland Street between City Road and South Dowling Street

FROM 3PM TO 11PM

  • Albion Street between Mary Street and Flinders Street (northern side)
  • Albion Street between Bourke Street and Flinders Street (southern side)
  • Chalmers Street between Cleveland Street and Devonshire Street (western side)
  • Fitzroy Street between South Dowling Street and Bourke Street (both sides)
  • Flinders Street between Albion Street and Moore Park Road (eastern side)
  • Foveaux Street between Bourke Street and Crown Street (northern side)
  • Lang Road between Cook Road and Anzac Parade (both sides)
  • Moore Park Road between Flinders Street and Driver Avenue (northern side)
  • Moore Park Road between Driver Avenue and Anzac Parade (southern side)

properties.headline: A-League - Friday 24 July - GOSFORD Dane Dr between Central Coast Hwy AND Donnison St
properties.otherAdvice:
A-League: Central Coast Mariners v Newcastle Jets at Central Coast Stadium from 7:30pm until 9:30pm.

Traffic may be heavier than normal on the Central Coast Hwy, Pacific Hwy, Brisbane Water Dr, Donnison St and Mann St as fans travel to and from the stadium.

Dane Dr between Georgiana Terrace and Donnison St will close from 5:30pm and re-open once crowds have safely cleared the area.

Fans driving to the game should allow extra travel time and be aware of changed traffic conditions.

Fans driving to the game should allow extra travel time for parking and be aware of changed traffic conditions.
